<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910715-0073</DOCNO><DOCID>910715-0073.</DOCID><HL>   Dow Chemical Credit Line   Is Increased to $3 Billion</HL><DATE>07/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17</SO><CO>   DOW</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><RE>MICHIGAN (MI)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MIDLAND, Mich. -- Dow Chemical Co. replaced asoon-to-expire $1 billion line of credit with a one-year pactfor $3 billion.   The chemicals company said it will use proceeds forgeneral corporate purposes, &quot;which may include acquisitions,support for Dow's commercial paper program and other capitalrequirements.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   The new pact boosts the company's total line of committedlines of credit to a hefty $5.4 billion.   Dow's release stressed that &quot;at this time,&quot; the company&quot;has not made any decisions regarding specific uses for anyborrowings under the credit agreement.&quot;   Citicorp's Citibank unit is agent for the syndicate ofbanks providing the new credit.</TEXT></DOC>